main event: An electronic engineer reported a sighting of a brilliant, cigar-shaped object over Anaheim, California on May 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object was brighter than immediate stars and changed color from white to red, blue, and green., The observation lasted for 4 minutes and the object traveled southerly at a 15 to 20 degree angle., The object varied in size, appearing to be 45-50 feet long and 17-18 feet wide when first sighted., The engineer suggested that it might have been a burn out after reentry., The object emitted no sound and left no trail, simply fading out of sight.
witness description: electronic engineer working on Project Apollo
